      scenario: 'Zava General Insurance Malaysia is a Malaysian general insurer with a large motor and commercial property book. Claims frequency stayed elevated after severe weather; the sharper problem is severity — repair inflation, leakage, and questionable workshop behaviour are pushing the motor portfolio beyond target while the reserve margin narrows. Detariffed pricing actions taken to defend market share are not fully compensating for the changing risk mix in segments where underwriting discipline weakened. BNM has asked for sharper explanations of reserve adequacy, reinsurance dependency, and the path back to a sustainable combined ratio before the next supervisory dialogue. Zava General Insurance Indonesia, the Indonesian affiliate, faces similar pressure as OJK reviews reserve assumptions, IDX investors question underwriting quality, and Bank Indonesia inflation keeps spare-parts costs high. The executive committee has two weeks to decide how hard to reprice, where to tighten claims controls, and whether reinsurance protection is still adequate.',
