      scenario: 'Zava Takaful Malaysia is a Malaysian takaful operator with family and general takaful lines; the immediate pressure sits in the participant fund and the wakalah model\'s competitiveness. Claims outgo has risen faster than expected in selected family takaful portfolios, lapse behaviour has worsened in the early years, and the current wakalah fee position looks uncomfortably high against newer digital competitors winning price-sensitive customers. A small number of Shariah process exceptions, not yet systemic, could become reputationally damaging if still open when BNM reviews governance, participant disclosure, and surplus treatment. The re-takaful programme is due for renewal as counterparties push for less generous terms, creating further uncertainty over protection and net fund resilience. The Indonesian affiliate Zava Takaful Indonesia faces similar scrutiny as OJK sharpens supervision of syariah fund governance, IDX investors question margin quality, and BI conditions influence participant affordability. Management has six weeks to decide whether to adjust fee strategy, tighten retention, and accelerate Shariah remediation.',
