      tagline: 'RevPAR slips at two flagship resorts, OTA commissions squeeze margin, and a Capex backlog meets an owner asset-management dispute.',
      scenario: 'Zava Hotels Malaysia is a Malaysian-listed hospitality group operating 14 properties across Indonesia (Bali, Lombok, Yogyakarta, Jakarta, Bintan), Malaysia and Vietnam — a mix of owned, leased, and third-party managed assets totalling 3,800 rooms and 9 F&B outlets per cluster. Group RevPAR fell 11% in the last quarter, two flagship resorts in Bali and Lombok are running 14-18% behind budget on RevPAR, OTA commissions have crept from 18% to 23% of net room revenue after recent re-tier changes by the two largest OTAs, a Capex maintenance backlog at three properties is now flagged Red on brand standards audit by Kemenparekraf and the franchise auditor, an owner of two managed properties has triggered an asset-management dispute over management fees and renovation pacing, and Bursa Malaysia has asked for a clarification after a sharp OTA-related disclosure from a regional peer. BPS tourism arrivals data show domestic short-haul demand softening into the September shoulder. The Group MD walks into a Board commercial and asset-management review in 7 days. The MD needs a defensible operations and commercial briefing pack, property-by-property RevPAR variance, OTA commission bridge, Capex re-prioritisation plan, owner holding lines, and a 90-day commercial and brand stabilisation programme.',
